Kassie Mowry is a renowned rodeo contestant and barrel racer, known for her exceptional skills in training horses and her impressive career earnings. Born on March 11, 1982, in Corona, California, Mowry has made a significant impact on the sport of barrel racing, with her first competition dating back to 1999. She has consistently demonstrated her prowess in the arena, earning recognition as a top futurity horse trainer.

Here we have Kassie Mowry’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Kassie Mowry

Kassie Mowry was born to parents Bill, a manager, and Kim, a massage therapist. She spent her early years in California before moving with her family to Utah during her teenage years. 

Despite her late start in barrel racing, Mowry had already developed a strong foundation in horsemanship skills and mental focus from her previous experience as an Olympic hopeful in eventing. 

This background has undoubtedly contributed to her success in the barrel racing arena.

Early Life

Raised in California and Utah, Mowry didn’t learn to run barrels until high school, although she had extensive experience in dressage and eventing. 

She was a teenager when she moved with her family from Orange County, California, to Utah and learned to run barrels.

As a former Olympic hopeful in eventing, Mowry had already developed the timing, horsemanship skills, and steely mental focus she uses today on the barrel pattern.

Professional Career

Mowry’s professional career took off in 1999 with her first competition. She has since established herself as a top futurity horse trainer, known for her ability to make a winner out of virtually any horse.

In 2006, Mowry started her own business training barrel horses and relocated to a 40-acre spread near Stephenville, Texas.

Over the years, she has racked up significant earnings, surpassing the $1 million mark in officially recorded barrel racing earnings in 2022 and reaching the elite $3 million mark in career earnings.

Kassie Mowry’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Kassie Mowry’s net worth is estimated to be $1 million.

She has earned significant income from her rodeo career. In 2023 alone, she earned over $133,802 in the regular season.

Career Earnings

Mowry’s career earnings are impressive. In 2022 alone, she won over $1 million in barrel racing. By 2019, she had reached the $3 million mark in career earnings. Her earnings through the 2023 regular season were reported to be $133,802.

Personal Details

Boyfriend

Kassie Mowry is in a relationship with Michael Boone, who is also her business partner. The couple owns many of the horses that Mowry rides each year and they work closely together, especially during the horses’ 2-year-old years.

How Old is Kassie Mowry?

As of November 27, 2023, Kassie Mowry is 41 years old.

What is her nationality?

She is American.

FAQs About Kassie Mowry 

When did Kassie Mowry start her professional career?

Kassie Mowry started her professional career in 1999.

What is her net worth in 2023?

As of 2023, her net worth is $1 million.

Who is her boyfriend?

Her boyfriend is Michael Boone.
